== PIP Image Processor ==

=== About ===

PIP stands for PIP Image Processor, which provides basic image processing interface for users.

It is a Digital Image Processing course project written in C++. (Previous versions contains C# and Java version, but C++ is currently used because it is required by DIP course.


=== What can PIP do ===
# Gray scale of a colored image
# Histogram of gray scale and RGB channel
# Threshold value using Otsu and Entropy Algorithm and customed value
# Border processing with black, nearest, mirror and periodic one
# Robert, Prewitt and Sobel operator
# Gaussian and Mean filter


